com.ibm.team.repository.common

Interface IReconcileReport


  • public interface IReconcileReport
    Represents the relative synchronization of two states of an auditable item and provides the information needs to reconcile any differences.
    Since:
    0.5

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static int CONFLICTING_UPDATES
      Kind constant indicating an outgoing update in conflict with an incoming update.
      static int INCOMING_CREATE
      Kind constant indicating an incoming item creation.
      static int INCOMING_UPDATE
      Kind constant indicating an incoming update, unopposed by any sort of outgoing change.
      static int NO_CHANGE
      Kind constant indicating nothing to reconcile.
      static int OUTGOING_CREATE
      Kind constant indicating an outgoing item creation.
      static int OUTGOING_UPDATE
      Kind constant indicating an outgoing update, unopposed by any sort of incoming change.

    • Method Detail

      • getKind

        int getKind()
        Returns the relative synchronization of two states of an auditable item.
        Returns:
        one of the kind constants declared on this interface

      • getOutgoing

        IAuditable getOutgoing()
        Returns the state of the item in the outgoing stream. This state may or may not be a working copy.
        Returns:
        the outgoing item state; never null

      • getIncoming

        IAuditable getIncoming()
        Returns the state of the item in the incoming stream. This state may or may not be a working copy.
        Returns:
        the incoming item state; never null

      • getBase

        IAuditable getBase()
        Returns the common base state shared between the incoming stream and outgoing streams. This is the state at which the streams diverged. This state is never a working copy. It is not applicable for creations.
        Returns:
        the base item state, or null if none

      • getMergeResult

        IAuditable getMergeResult()
        Returns the new state of the item which the client should modify to represent the result of merging the incoming changes with the outgoing changes. Always a working copy, and likely an alias for either the incoming or outgoing state. This is only applicable for conflicting updates.
        Returns:
        the merge item working copy, or null if none
